@startuml "Ionosense HPC - Streaming Executor Memory"
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam classBackgroundColor #E6FFE6
skinparam classBorderColor #228B22
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #E6FFE6
skinparam arrowColor #228B22

title Ionosense HPC - StreamingExecutor Memory Layout (v0.9.4+)
footer IEEE Publication Quality Diagram - © 2025 | Created: 2025-01-19

note top
  **StreamingExecutor Mode**: Low-latency streaming, arbitrary chunk sizes
  Total Memory: ~295 KB (nfft=2048, channels=2) **+80% vs BatchExecutor**
end note

package "Host Memory Space" #E6FFE6 {
  class "Input Chunk\n(float*)" as HostInput {
    size: variable (arbitrary)
    layout: per-channel chunks
  }

  class "Output Buffer\n(float*)" as HostOutput {
    size: (nfft/2+1) * channels
    layout: magnitude (per frame)
  }

  package "Ring Buffers (Per-Channel)" #C4E6C4 {
    class "RingBuffer[0]" as RingBuf0 <<lock-free>> {
      capacity: 3 * nfft
      write_pos: atomic<size_t>
      read_pos: atomic<size_t>
      available: atomic<size_t>
      buffer: PinnedHostBuffer
    }

    class "RingBuffer[1]" as RingBuf1 <<lock-free>> {
      capacity: 3 * nfft
      write_pos: atomic<size_t>
      read_pos: atomic<size_t>
      available: atomic<size_t>
      buffer: PinnedHostBuffer
    }

    note right of RingBuf0
      **Per-channel ring buffer**
      - Accumulates arbitrary chunks
      - 3× NFFT capacity prevents overflow
      - Lock-free thread-safe (SPSC)
      - Pinned memory for fast transfers
    end note
  }

  class "h_batch_staging" as Staging <<page-locked>> {
    size: nfft * channels
    purpose: frame extraction buffer
    note: Extracted frames from ring buffers
  }

  class "PinnedHostBuffer[0]\ninput_staging" as Pinned0 <<page-locked>> {
    size: nfft * channels
    purpose: double buffering
  }

  class "PinnedHostBuffer[1]\noutput_staging" as Pinned1 <<page-locked>> {
    size: (nfft/2+1) * channels
    purpose: double buffering
  }
}

package "Device Memory Space" #FFD700 {
  class "DeviceBuffer[0]\nInput" as DevInput0 {
    size: nfft * channels * sizeof(float)
    stride: nfft
    layout: per-channel
  }

  class "DeviceBuffer[1]\nInput" as DevInput1 {
    size: nfft * channels * sizeof(float)
    stride: nfft
    layout: per-channel
  }

  class "DeviceBuffer\nIntermediate" as DevIntermediate {
    size: (nfft/2+1) * channels * sizeof(float2)
    format: complex (R2C output)
    note: Hermitian symmetry
  }

  class "DeviceBuffer\nOutput" as DevOutput {
    size: (nfft/2+1) * channels * sizeof(float)
    format: magnitude
    layout: [ch0_bins, ch1_bins, ...]
  }

  class "Window Coefficients" as WindowCoef <<cached>> {
    size: nfft * sizeof(float)
    precomputed: true
  }

  class "cuFFT Work Area" as WorkArea {
    size: dynamic
    managed by: CufftPlan
  }
}

package "PCIe Transfer" <<Transport>> #FFE4E4 {
  class "H2D Stream[0]" as H2D
  class "D2H Stream[2]" as D2H
}

' Data flow - Streaming mode
HostInput --> RingBuf0 : push(chunk[ch0])
HostInput --> RingBuf1 : push(chunk[ch1])

RingBuf0 --> Staging : extract_batch(nfft, 1, hop_size)
RingBuf1 --> Staging : extract_batch(nfft, 1, hop_size)

Staging --> H2D : async
H2D --> DevInput0 : cudaMemcpyAsync

DevInput0 --> DevInput0 : window (in-place)
DevInput0 --> DevIntermediate : FFT (R2C)
DevIntermediate --> DevOutput : magnitude

DevOutput --> D2H : async
D2H --> Pinned1 : cudaMemcpyAsync
Pinned1 --> HostOutput : memcpy

WindowCoef --> DevInput0 : element-wise mult

RingBuf0 --> RingBuf0 : advance(hop_size) after frame
RingBuf1 --> RingBuf1 : advance(hop_size) after frame

note bottom
  **StreamingExecutor Memory Breakdown**:
  - Ring buffers: 3 × nfft × channels × sizeof(float) = **98 KB** (extra)
  - Staging buffer: nfft × channels × sizeof(float) = **33 KB** (extra)
  - Device buffers: same as BatchExecutor = **164 KB**
  - **Total: ~295 KB (+80% overhead vs BatchExecutor)**

  **Tradeoffs**:
  ✅ Supports arbitrary input chunk sizes
  ✅ Continuous streaming capability
  ✅ Per-channel independence
  ❌ +80% memory overhead
  ❌ +40% latency (122.25 µs vs 86.79 µs)

  **Ring Buffer Operations**:
  1. push() - Add new samples (lock-free)
  2. can_extract(nfft) - Check if full frame available
  3. extract_batch() - Extract overlapping frames
  4. advance(hop_size) - Move read pointer for overlap

  **Capacity: 3× NFFT rationale**:
  - Prevents overflow during pipeline warmup
  - Allows safe accumulation before first extraction
  - Handles bursty input patterns
end note

@enduml
